    dc:title "New Antocha Osten Sacken (Diptera: Limoniidae) from Sichuan, China" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4749009>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4749013>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4749019>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4749021>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4749015>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4749023> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4749009>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–10. Distinctive features of genus Antocha in Sichuan, China. 1. wing of A. pulchra sp. nov., paratype; 2. wing of A. nigribasis, paratype from Markevičiūtė et al. (2019, fig. 11); 3. male tergite 9 of A. pallidella, from Alexander (1933, fig. 37); 4. male tergite 9 of A. nigribasis, from Alexander (1932, fig. 42); 5. male tergite 9 of A. emarginata, holotype from Markevičiūtė et al. (2019, fig. 9); 6. male gonocoxite, gonostyli and tergite 9 of A. fortidens; 7. male gonocoxite, gonostyli and tergite 9 of A. nebulipennis immaculata; 8. male gonocoxite, gonostyli and tergite 9 of A. nebulipennis nebulipennis from Markevičiūtė et al. (2019, figs 46, 49); 9. male tergite 9 from Alexander (1932, fig. 43) and genital structures of A. bidens, holotype; 10. male tergite 9 and genital structures of A. bifida." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4749009/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4749013>
    dc:description "FIGURES 11–15. Distinctive features of genus Antocha in Sichuan, China. 11. male genitalia and genital structures, dorsal view of A. spiralis; 12. male genital structures and tergite 9 of A. constricta; 13. male genital structures and tergite 9 of A. multidentata; 14. male genital structures and tergite 9 of A. quadrifurca; 15. male genital structures and tergite 9 of A. pulchra sp. nov., paratype." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4749013/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4749019>
    dc:description "FIGURES 21–27. Antocha (Antocha) pulchra sp. nov. 21. male habitus, holotype; 22. male antenna, paratype; 23. male wing, paratype; 24. male tergite 9, paratype; 25. male sternite 9, paratype; 26. male genitalia, dorsal view, paratype; 27. male genital structures and aedeagus, dorsal view, paratype." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4749019/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4749021>
    dc:description "FIGURE 28. Type locality of Antocha (Antocha) pulchra sp. nov." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4749021/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4749015>
    dc:description "FIGURES 16–20. Distinctive features of genus Antocha in Sichuan, China. 16. male genitalia, dorsal view of A. minuticornis, holotype from Markevičiūtė et al. (2019, fig. 21); 17. male gonocoxite and gonostyli of A. lacteibasis, paratype; 18. male genital structures and tergite 9 of A. setigera, paratype; 19. male genital structures and tergite 9 of A. indica; 20. male genital structures and tergite 9 of A. bella, paratype from Markevičiūtė et al. (2019, figs 12, 26, 28)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4749015/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4749023>
    dc:description "FIGURES 29–35. Antocha (Antocha) quadrifurca. 29. male antenna; 30. male wing; 31. male genital structures and aedeagus, dorsal view; 32. male sternite 9; 33. male tergite 9; 34. male genitalia, lateral view; 35. male genitalia, dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4749023/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

